{
  "title": "From IVR to Conversational AI: Designing a Voice Agent That Works for Everyone",
  "subtitle": "A case study in conversational design, personality-driven dialogue, and human-centered automation.",
  "metadata": [
    {
      "label": "Problem to solve",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "eDreams Odigeo's voice support suffered from a fundamental design flaw: the IVR was obstructive. Customers called in with complex issues and it was hard to fit them into the traditional IVR system, which forced them into rigid menu trees. The gap between system and customer mental model was creating friction, frustration and high transfer rates."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "label": "Main Impact",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "strong",
          "value": "By May 2026"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": " (5 months post-MVP launch), across 12.5k tracked calls:"
        },
        {
          "type": "break"
        },
        {
          "type": "strong",
          "value": "Transfer Rate (Overall)"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": ": 16.9% → 15.4% (↓ 8.9%)"
        },
        {
          "type": "break"
        },
        {
          "type": "strong",
          "value": "Authentication Rate"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": ": 33.1% → 55% (↑ 65.8%)"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "label": "Timeline",
      "value": "March 2025 – May 2026 (13 months, MVP to scale)"
    }
    
  ],
