          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "labeled",
          "label": [
            {
              "type": "strong",
              "value": "User Experience:"
            }
          ],
          "list": [
            [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "value": "Average conversation duration: 1min 24sec (intent recognition + resolution)"
              }
            ],
            [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "value": "Intent classification accuracy: 72–100% by language (EN leading)"
              }
            ],
            [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "value": "Customers completed 6.6% of complex queries autonomously (early booking confirmation agent)"
              }
            ]
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Insights",
      "subsections": [
        {
          "label": [
            {
              "type": "strong",
              "value": "Tone is Architecture"
            }
          ],
          "blocks": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": "Personality isn't the last thing you add before ship, it's a structural design decision. It shapes which information you gather first, how you phrase questions, how you handle errors, and what the customer feels throughout. Different personas should have measurably different conversation flows and different success metrics."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "label": [
            {
              "type": "strong",
              "value": "Handoff Design Matters as Much as Automation"
            }
          ],
          "blocks": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": "The real value wasn't \"bots handling everything.\" It was bots preparing the ground so that when a human stepped in, they could actually help—not restart."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": "Design for the agent as much as the customer. Dialogue systems should be passing context, not just transferring calls."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "label": [
            {
              "type": "strong",
              "value": "Specialization Reduces Hallucinations"
            }
          ],
          "blocks": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": "A single \"general\" agent trying to handle refunds, bookings, and baggage is a hallucination waiting to happen. Focused agents with narrow scope outperform. This is a design principle, not just an engineering one."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "label": [
            {
              "type": "strong",
              "value": "Temporal Design Requires Different Skills"
            }
          ],
          "blocks": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": "Designing for voice/chat is categorically different from screen design. Pixels give you space to show options. Dialogue gives you time to build them in turns. Scripts, emotional arcs, and dialogue states become your core design artifacts, not wireframes."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "label": [
            {
              "type": "strong",
              "value": "Test the Repair Paths, Not Just the Happy Path"
            }
          ],
          "blocks": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": "The best conversational experiences fail gracefully. What happens when the bot is confused? When the user says something unexpected? When the system can't authenticate? The repair paths are where personality either holds together or breaks down."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
